          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Used to plot the checkout progress and communicate what stage in the process they are on, what's completed and what's left. </p>
  
            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There are two main layout modes for this component: desktop and mobile. Larger screens show the display as a horizontal process diagram. Smaller screens are give signposting for the position they are in, inside the process.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <h4>Media queries</h4>
            <p>We are using three breakpoints to handle the changes between desktop, tablet and mobile. Common styles are loaded for the component and then device specific styles are loaded in for each breakpoint into the appropriate stylesheet.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/large-components/checkout-process.scss</p>
            <p>/tablet-components/checkout-process.scss</p>
            <p>/small-components/checkout-process.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>There are three visible steps to this process. The variants assume the login step is currently outside of this application. The Checkout process illustrates a user's journey through the single page checkout, review details and confirmations steps.</p>
          </div>
